Class Filopart

  • java.lang.Object

    FiloPod

    public class Filopart
extends java.lang.Object
implements FiloPod
    Represents a 2-dimensional filopodium. Stores Rois, time and part indices, coordinates and statistics.

    Richard Butler

      • getLength

        public double getLength()
        Estimate the length of this filopodium as half perimeter corrected for width.

        width factor w = 2 * sqrt(2*log(2)) * sigma
        estimate correction EC = ((PI - 2)/2) * w
        distance D = distance from the base to the tip
        scale factor SF = min( (D/w)^2, 1d )

        estimated length = perimeter/2 - EC * SF

        Specified by:
        getLength in interface FiloPod
        Returns:
        The estimated length
